      <p>@Jen-  they are called &#39;Toas-Tites  &quot;for drip-proof sandwiches sealed in golden toast&quot;  I have an original booklet and an iron that was post WWII.   The iron pressed the edges of the bread together, and made a sort-of &#39;hot pocket&#39;.  ;)</p>

